+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UdSQYVsyKzeWvPdaJ5tqJQ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now let me create a comprehensive summary document.\n\n## Complete Codebase Structure - Event-Driven Order Processing System\n\n### Source Files (10 total)\n\n#### Core Entry Point\n**`/workspace/src/index.ts`**\n- Main export file for the entire module\n- Re-exports EventBus, event types, and all service classes (OrderService, InventoryService, BillingService, NotificationService)\n- Re-exports repository classes (OrderRepository, InventoryRepository)\n- Re-exports type definitions (Order, OrderItem, OrderStatus, StockRecord, PaymentRecord, PriceBreakdown, NotificationRecord)\n- Provides single entry point for consumers of the library\n\n#### Events Module (2 files)\n**`/workspace/src/events/types.ts`**\n- Defines TypeScript interfaces for all order-related events\n- Exports event types: OrderEvent (base), OrderCreatedEvent, OrderCancelledEvent, OrderRefundedEvent, PaymentChargedEvent, StockReservedEvent\n- Exports ORDER_EVENTS constant object with event type names: CREATED, CONFIRMED, CANCELLED, REFUNDED, PAYMENT_CHARGED, STOCK_RESERVED, STOCK_RELEASED, NOTIFICATION_SENT\n- Uses discriminated union pattern with OrderEvent base interface\n\n**`/workspace/src/events/bus.ts`**\n- Implements an in-memory event bus for pub/sub communication\n- Provides EventBus class with methods: on (subscribe), off (unsubscribe), emit (publish), clear (reset)\n- Uses module-level globalHandlers Map for handler registry (shared across all EventBus instances)\n- Supports async event handlers\n- Core infrastructure for event-driven architecture\n\n#### Orders Module (2 files)\n**`/workspace/src/orders/repository.ts`**\n- Defines Order and OrderItem interfaces\n- Defines OrderStatus type: 'pending' | 'confirmed' | 'cancelled' | 'refunded'\n- Implements OrderRepository class with in-memory Map storage\n- Methods: create, findById, update, findByCustomer, findByStatus, clear\n- Returns defensive copies of orders (prevents external mutation)\n\n**`/workspace/src/orders/service.ts`**\n- Implements OrderService class for order lifecycle management\n- Constructor dependencies: OrderRepository, EventBus, BillingService\n- Methods:\n  - `createOrder`: Creates order, emits CREATED event, charges payment via BillingService, emits CONFIRMED event\n  - `cancelOrder`: Validates order status, emits CANCELLED event, updates status\n  - `refundOrder`: Checks 30-day refund window, issues refund via BillingService\n  - `getOrder`: Retrieves single order\n  - `getOrdersByCustomer`: Retrieves all orders for a customer\n- Core order processing logic with event emission and payment integration\n\n#### Billing Module (2 files)\n**`/workspace/src/billing/calculator.ts`**\n- Pure utility function: `calculateOrderTotal`\n- Input: OrderItem[], discountPercent, taxRate\n- Returns PriceBreakdown interface with: subtotal, discountAmount, taxAmount, total\n- Performs precise decimal calculations (rounds to 2 decimal places)\n- No side effects or dependencies\n\n**`/workspace/src/billing/service.ts`**\n- Implements BillingService class for payment processing\n- Constructor dependencies: EventBus, NotificationService\n- Methods:\n  - `chargePayment`: Calculates total using calculator, creates PaymentRecord, stores in Map, sends confirmation notification\n  - `issueRefund`: Updates payment status to 'refunded', emits REFUNDED event, sends refund notification\n  - `getPayment`: Retrieves payment record for an order\n  - `registerHandlers`: Subscribes to STOCK_RESERVED and REFUNDED events\n  - `clear`: Clears payment records\n- Event handlers: handleStockReserved, handleRefund\n- Integrates with NotificationService\n\n#### Inventory Module (2 files)\n**`/workspace/src/inventory/repository.ts`**\n- Defines StockRecord interface with: productId, available, reserved\n- Implements InventoryRepository class with in-memory Map storage\n- Methods:\n  - `setStock`: Sets available stock for a product\n  - `getStock`: Retrieves stock record\n  - `reserve`: Decreases available, increases reserved (returns boolean for success/failure)\n  - `release`: Increases available, decreases reserved (returns boolean for success/failure)\n  - `clear`: Clears all stock records\n- Tracks both available and reserved inventory\n\n**`/workspace/src/inventory/service.ts`**\n- Implements InventoryService class for stock management\n- Constructor dependencies: InventoryRepository, EventBus\n- Methods:\n  - `setStock`: Sets available stock for a product\n  - `getStock`: Retrieves stock record\n  - `registerHandlers`: Subscribes to CREATED and CANCELLED events\n- Event handlers:\n  - `handleOrderCreated`: Reserves stock for all order items, with rollback on failure, emits STOCK_RESERVED event\n  - `handleOrderCancelled`: Releases reserved stock, emits STOCK_RELEASED event\n- Implements inventory reservation pattern with transactional semantics\n\n#### Notifications Module (1 file)\n**`/workspace/src/notifications/service.ts`**\n- Implements NotificationService class for order notifications\n- Constructor sets up template Map for: order.confirmed, order.cancelled, order.refunded\n- Methods:\n  - `sendConfirmation`: Sends order confirmation with total amount\n  - `sendCancellation`: Sends cancellation notice with reason\n  - `sendRefundNotice`: Sends refund notification with amount\n  - `getSentNotifications`: Returns all sent notifications\n  - `clear`: Clears notification history\n- Returns NotificationRecord with: type, orderId, message, sentAt timestamp\n- Template-based message generation with placeholder replacement\n\n---\n\n### Test Files (5 total)\n\n| Test File | Location |\n|-----------|----------|\n| **`/workspace/tests/billing.test.ts`** | Tests for BillingService and calculateOrderTotal |\n| **`/workspace/tests/events.test.ts`** | Tests for EventBus functionality |\n| **`/workspace/tests/inventory.test.ts`** | Tests for InventoryService and InventoryRepository |\n| **`/workspace/tests/notifications.test.ts`** | Tests for NotificationService |\n| **`/workspace/tests/orders.test.ts`** | Tests for OrderService and OrderRepository |\n\n---\n\n### Architecture Overview\n\n**Event-Driven Pattern**: The system uses a central EventBus for decoupled communication between services\n- OrderService creates orders and emits events\n- InventoryService listens to order events and manages stock\n- BillingService listens to stock events and processes payments\n- NotificationService is invoked directly by BillingService\n\n**Key Event Flow**:\n1. Order created → ORDER_CREATED event\n2. Stock reserved → STOCK_RESERVED event\n3. Payment charged → PAYMENT_CHARGED event\n4. Order confirmed → ORDER_CONFIRMED event\n5. Order cancelled → ORDER_CANCELLED event → stock released\n6. Refund issued → REFUNDED event\n\n**Storage**: All services use in-memory Map-based repositories for data persistence"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a75368a (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 22378\ntool_uses: 15\nduration_ms: 25112</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"89853c70-574b-4e21-b30e-5cf7add4d971","uuid":"ec4f1589-51e4-4971-9698-a4be90b5064f","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase at /workspace. I need to understand the full structure of the event-driven order processing system. List all source files (not test files) under src/, and give me a brief summary of what each file does. Also list the test files separately. Be very thorough - list every file.","agentId":"a75368a","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now let me create a comprehensive summary document.\n\n## Complete Codebase Structure - Event-Driven Order Processing System\n\n### Source Files (10 total)\n\n#### Core Entry Point\n**`/workspace/src/index.ts`**\n- Main export file for the entire module\n- Re-exports EventBus, event types, and all s